================================================================================
HOW TO RUN THE PROGRAM
================================================================================

Follow these steps to run the project in BlueJ or any Java environment.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1. OPEN THE PROJECT
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
- Launch BlueJ
- Open the folder containing all .java files

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2. COMPILE ALL CLASSES
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
- Click "Compile" (top-left)
- Ensure no errors appear
- If errors appear, recompile classes in this order:
      Enums → Game → Subclasses → GameLibrary → RatingLibrary → GameSession

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
3. CREATE A GAMELIBRARY OBJECT
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
- Right-click GameLibrary
- Select:  new GameLibrary()

This object will store all games.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
4. ADD GAMES TO THE LIBRARY
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Use the GameLibrary methods:

- addGame(title, genre, ageRating, platform)
- or create subclass objects manually:
      new SinglePlayerGame(...)
      new OnlineGame(...)
      new MultiplayerGame(...)

Then insert them into the library if needed.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
5. SEARCH, FILTER, AND LIST GAMES
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Use:
- list()
- listByGenre()
- listByPlatform()
- listByRating()
- search()

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
6. START A GAME SESSION
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
- Create a GameSession object:
      new GameSession(game, duration)

- Call:
      startSession()

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
7. RATE GAMES OR ADD COMMENTS
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
- Create RatingLibrary
- Use:
      rateGame(game, rating)
      addComments(game, "text")
      printWritings(game)

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
8. VIEW DETAILS
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
- Call toString() on any Game or subclass
- Call printLibraryDetails() on GameLibrary

